˛26U<?php exit; ?>a:6:{s:10:"last_error";s:0:"";s:10:"last_query";s:60:"SELECT wp_posts.* FROM wp_posts WHERE ID IN (1862,1863,1864)";s:11:"last_result";a:3:{i:0;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1862";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-07-22 21:22:14";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-07-22 21:22:14";s:12:"post_content";s:3438:"<b data-fallback-processed="true">1. Affordable¬†</b>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">One of the main advantages of hiring fresh graduates is that hiring them is less expensive than hiring more experienced professionals. This doesn‚Äôt mean that you can hire a fresh graduate and pay them extremely low salaries, i.e. salaries that are way lower than the market rate, but it provides an opportunity for a company to hire a talented individual at an entry-level rate and invest in them so they become star employees for your company.</p>
<br data-fallback-processed="true" /><b data-fallback-processed="true">2. Innovative Ideas, Fresh Perspective¬†</b>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">Fresh graduates might have done a few internships, but they haven‚Äôt yet been instilled into the corporate world. Their mind isn‚Äôt tainted with previous company practices. As such, they can bring a new perspective to your organization. Most universities emphasize on the importance of innovation, which these graduates bring to the table. Fresh grads might be able to point out flaws which are unseen by the current staff.</p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true"><br data-fallback-processed="true" /><b data-fallback-processed="true">3. Masters of Continuous Learning¬†</b></p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">Fresh graduates are often eager to learn and extremely determined to prove themselves. When given a task they tackle it wholeheartedly. They‚Äôre not afraid of asking questions, as they‚Äôre trained to do so in college. Being similar to a ‚Äúblank canvas‚Äù, they can adapt to any corporate culture easily. They‚Äôre also open to new ideas and working styles.</p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true"><b data-fallback-processed="true">4. Technical and Business Skills¬†</b></p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">Numerous technical skills are taught to graduates in college such as computer skills. Other skills they acquire are administration skills, communication and problem solving skills, and so forth. Their analyzing and critical thinking capabilities are at a peak at this time. The subject matter is fresh in their mind and they might be able to apply these terms and concepts for the betterment of your organization.</p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true"><br data-fallback-processed="true" /><b data-fallback-processed="true">5. Commitment, Commitment &amp; More Commitment¬†</b></p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">Fresh graduates usually do not have familial commitments. They usually fend for themselves. Due to this, they display more commitment towards work. Older individuals with family ties will have a harder time trying to balance their work and family time. Fresh graduates might be willing to work longer hours and take up additional projects.</p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true"><br data-fallback-processed="true" /><b data-fallback-processed="true">6. Tech Wizards¬†</b></p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">The generation gap becomes evident when it comes to technology. Both millennials and the older generation agree that technology makes them effective at work. Three quarters of those below 35 believe that older colleagues do not take full advantage of technology available. On the other hand, youngsters are able to type on a keyboard or on their mobile at an unmatchable rate. They know how to keep up with the latest technological trends and they can bring this, as an asset, to any job.</p>";s:10:"post_title";s:34:"5 Reasons To Hire a Fresh Graduate";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:34:"5-reasons-to-hire-a-fresh-graduate";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-04-21 12:18:20";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-04-21 04:18:20";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:41:"http://demo.astoundify.com/jobify/?p=1862";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:1;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1863";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-07-22 21:22:14";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-07-22 21:22:14";s:12:"post_content";s:3734:"<b data-fallback-processed="true">1. Start Doing Actual Work¬†</b>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">The feeling you get when you work for a startup is rather hard to describe. It‚Äôs a little like taking the red pill and getting a shot in the arm. Everything you do makes a difference. In a startup, everything you do will contribute to the ultimate success or failure of the business, you can make or break the venture! Startups actually push you to identify and focus on what‚Äôs absolutely critical, forcing you to think more creatively about how you approach projects and create value. And best of all, you‚Äôll often get to see results first-hand and share in the rewards and glory.</p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true"><b data-fallback-processed="true">2. Learning &amp; Responsibilities¬†</b></p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">You typically learn more in your first 2 months in a startup than in 5 years at a larger company. The reason for this is that everyone in a startup is expected to wear multiple hats. A startup forces you to adopt new skills and responsibilities to make up for the small-sized taking on the huge challenges of building an empire.¬†In startups, fast learning can also lead to increased responsibility and multiple opportunities to both utilize and accelerate talents and knowledge. All of this can translate into powerful position in the business world and means you‚Äôll have much more to offer as an individual, particularly when it's time to move on or even start your own¬†venture.</p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true"><strong data-fallback-processed="true">3. Shape The Company Culture¬†</strong></p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">There‚Äôs nothing more rewarding than feeling excited to come into the office in the morning to tackle the next challenge the world has thrown at you.</p>
You will also find that in startups, you get to shape the culture around you. Entering a larger organization usually means that you‚Äôll be stepping into a predetermined culture, set with existing practices, customs and values. Joining a startup, on the other hand, often means that you can directly contribute to the creation and growth of the business culture, offering ideas and practices that can help shape the working philosophy of the company.<br data-fallback-processed="true" /><strong data-fallback-processed="true"><br data-fallback-processed="true" />4. Innovation All Around You¬†<br data-fallback-processed="true" /></strong>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">One of the most rewarding things about startups is that you can find yourself working with a team that is highly passionate and enthusiastic. This can spark inspiration on every level, leading to truly innovative ideas and developments that can help the business stand out against competitors in the greater industry.</p>
Being part of an entrepreneurial team is also a wonderful way to learn how to innovate. Entrepreneurs are great people to learn from ‚Äî they identify a problem and need to find a new efficient way to solve it.<br data-fallback-processed="true" /><br data-fallback-processed="true" /><b data-fallback-processed="true">5. Branch Out On You Own¬†</b>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">Joining a startup gives you the opportunity to start learning what it takes to be your own boss. While¬†they take personal and financial sacrifice, startups pay you back in opportunities and knowledge on how to take charge of your own venture.</p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">If you‚Äôre toying with the idea of one day being your own boss, working in a startup is the ideal place to educate yourself on how to set goals, execute strategies, take your product to market and implement strong business.W</p>";s:10:"post_title";s:32:"Why You Should Work In a Startup";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:32:"why-you-should-work-in-a-startup";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-04-21 12:11:19";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-04-21 04:11:19";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:41:"http://demo.astoundify.com/jobify/?p=1863";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:2;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:4:"1864";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2013-07-22 21:22:14";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2013-07-22 21:22:14";s:12:"post_content";s:2823:"Part time work is becoming an increasingly popular trend in Malaysia with more and more students signing up for jobs in malls and cafes nearby. Here's a few reasons why we think it's a brilliant idea:

&nbsp;

<b data-fallback-processed="true">Cash Flow Is Never Bad¬†</b>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">Call me Mr. Obvious, but this is one of the greatest perks of working part-time while in university. Having a steady income allows you to settle debts¬†quicker, leaving you with less financial stress after graduation. Students don‚Äôt realize how much little things cost while at university (gas, coffee and books) and having an income helps you stay out of dipping into savings to buy the ‚Äúextras‚Äù.</p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true"></p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true"><b data-fallback-processed="true">Develop¬†Useful Skills¬†</b></p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">Even though you may not think the skills you‚Äôre developing at a part-time job will be useful to your career, they can be! Part-time jobs teach skills every employer is looking for: commitment, time management, teamwork, leadership,¬†organization, customer service ‚Äì the list goes on! So put yourself out there and your resume will thank you for it.</p>
&nbsp;
<p data-fallback-processed="true"><b data-fallback-processed="true">Gives You a Break¬†</b></p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">During college, it‚Äôs easy to feel as though you‚Äôre in a bubble filled with classes, studying, projects, friends and late nights. It‚Äôs not a bad bubble to be in, but sometimes we all need a quick break from student life. Having a part-time job allows you to get out of the library and away from your roommates, giving you a much-needed break from the hustle and bustle of being a student.</p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true"></p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true"><b data-fallback-processed="true">Improves Grades</b></p>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">This might be surprising but it‚Äôs true! When your only commitment is your studies, you may think you have all the time in the world to finish school work. This may result in a less effective work ethic. Having a job forces you to manage your time and organize your tasks in a productive and effective manner. The amount of hours a student can handle varies, but for the most part, when employers hire on students they are aware that the priority is education (especially in Malaysia) and will work with you to make it a win-win situation.</p>
&nbsp;

<b data-fallback-processed="true">Networking Opportunities¬†</b>
<p data-fallback-processed="true">Working a part-time job allows you to develop connections. You may get a great friend, reference, connection or even full-time job after school from committing to a sustainable number of hours each week!</p>";s:10:"post_title";s:49:"Why a Part Time Job While Studying is a Good Idea";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:49:"why-a-part-time-job-while-studying-is-a-good-idea";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2015-04-21 12:23:47";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2015-04-21 04:23:47";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:41:"http://demo.astoundify.com/jobify/?p=1864";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}}s:8:"col_info";a:23:{i:0;O:8:"stdClass":13:{s:4:"name";s:2:"ID";s:5:"table";s:8:"wp_posts";s:3:"def";s:0:"";s:10:"max_length";i:4;s:8:"not_null";i:1;s:11:"primary_key";i:1;s:12:"multiple_key";i:0;s:10:"unique_key";i:0;s:7:"numeric";i:1;s:4:"blob";i:0;s:4:"type";s:3:"int";s:8:"unsigned";i:1;s:8:"zerofill";i:0;}i:1;O:8:"stdClass":13:{s:4:"name";s:11:"post_author";s:5:"table";s:8:"wp_posts";s:3:"def";s:0:"";s:10:"max_length";i:1;s:8:"not_null";i:1;s:11:"primary_key";i:0;s:12:"multiple_key";i:1;s:10:"unique_key";i:0;s:7:"numeric";i:1;s:4:"blob";i:0;s:4:"type";s:3:"int";s:8:"unsigned";i:1;s:8:"zerofill";i:0;}i:2;O:8:"stdClass":13:{s:4:"name";s:9:"post_date";s:5:"table";s:8:"wp_posts";s:3:"def";s:0:"";s:10:"max_length";i:19;s:8:"not_null";i:1;s:11:"primary_key";i:0;s:12:"multiple_key";i:0;s:10:"unique_key";i:0;s:7:"numeric";i:0;s:4:"blob";i:0;s:4:"type";s:8:"datetime";s:8:"unsigned";i:0;s:8:"zerofill";i:0;}i:3;O:8:"stdClass":13:{s:4:"name";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:5:"table";s:8:"wp_posts";s:3:"def";s:0:"";s:10:"max_length";i:19;s:8:"not_null";i:1;s:11:"primary_key";i:0;s:1